components.name: React Components
components.description: Reusable UI elements that manage their own state and can be composed to build complex interfaces.

components.name: React DOM
components.description: The package that provides DOM-specific methods for rendering React components to the web.

components.name: Babel Compiler
components.description: Transpiles modern JavaScript and JSX into backward-compatible JavaScript, enabling the use of the latest language features.

components.name: Webpack
components.description: A module bundler that compiles JavaScript modules and assets, optimizing them for production.

data_flows.description: React components render their output to the DOM through the React DOM package.
Babel processes source code and outputs transpiled code, which is then bundled by Webpack.

trust_boundaries.name: Client-Side Trust Boundary
trust_boundaries.description: The boundary between the user's browser and the server, where user inputs are processed.

trust_boundaries.name: Build Process Trust Boundary
trust_boundaries.description: The boundary during the build process where source code is transformed and bundled.
